{
  "rule": "vertical_remap",
  "applicable": false,
  "skip_reason": "vertical_remap is a conservative-remap *scheme* (Lin 2004 PPM-based vertical remap), not a fixed-neighbor stencil. Its application requires (a) a conservative-remap rule type to be added to the ESS §7 schema (tracked in docs/rule-catalog.md, `vertical_remap_lin_2004` row: schema_gaps = `needs conservative-remap rule type`) and (b) time-varying per-cell vertical metric bindings (tracked in discretizations/SELECTOR_KINDS.md decision #3). Until the harness can bind dp_old[k] / dp_new[k] as per-column, time-varying inputs and lower a data-dependent overlap sweep, the convergence-fixture model is not the right shape for this rule. Numeric coverage of the constant-, conservation-, and monotonicity-properties already lives at test/test_vertical_remap.jl against the runtime path src/operators/vertical_remap.jl. A follow-up bead will retire that runtime path and migrate the same checks under conservation/ and monotonicity/ here once the schema extensions land."
}
